snippet.title: B&O BeoPlay H3 and H6 aluminium headphones treat your ears
snippet.description: If you want to treat your ears, splash out on the Bang and Olufsen BeoPlay H3 and H6, made from aluminium and happy cows.

snippet.title: Nokia Lumia 920 sequel could be skinnier, made of aluminium
snippet.description: Nokia is apparently considering building its next flagship from aluminium, making it both thinner and lighter.

snippet.title: iPad mini glimpsed with nano-SIM slot and aluminium case
snippet.description: Bits and pieces of the hotly-tipped iPad mini have appeared online, giving us a glimpse of the rumoured sawn-off 7-inch iPad.

snippet.title: Sony Xperia tablet leaks with splash-proof aluminium frame
snippet.description: Sony's plotting another Android tablet that looks the same as its earlier Tablet S. Read on for the details.

snippet.title: iPhone 5 rumoured to have aluminium rear and A5 processor
snippet.description: With the iPad 2 now official, it's time for the iPhone 5 rumour-mill to start cranking out speculation in earnest. Today's instalment suggests an aluminium back and a beefy processor for the device.

snippet.title: HTC Desire S has a lot to live up to with Android 2.4 in an aluminium unibody
snippet.description: HTC has announced the next object of desire in its Android-packing phone line-up: the HTC Desire S. Will it match up to its illustrious predecessors?

snippet.title: Iriver E150, E200 to go aluminium, lose speakers
snippet.description: It's getting rid of the plastic chassis, replacing it with an iPod nano-esque aluminium casing.

snippet.title: iRiver E150, E200 to go aluminium and lose speakers
snippet.description: We've just had some hot-off-the-press updates from iRiver concerning the successors to the E100 MP3 player, to be called the E150 or E200

snippet.title: Avantgarde Acoustics Zero 1 is a 10,000 Euro iPhone speaker
snippet.description: Got a spare 10,000 Euro burning a hole in your Swiss bank account? Here's an all-digital audiophile speaker that's just the job.

snippet.title: Samsung Galaxy S5 could be first metal Galaxy phone
snippet.description: Reports suggest the Samsung Galaxy S5 -- follow-up to the smash hit Galaxy S4 -- could boast the Galaxy line-up's first metal body.
